## Project coding rules for Cursor

- **Languages & stack**
  - Primary stack: plain `HTML`, `TailwindCSS` (via `src/style.css` / `output.css`), and vanilla `JavaScript` in `src/main.js`.
  - Prefer **Tailwind utilities** or `@apply` in `src/style.css` instead of writing raw CSS properties when possible.

- **HTML structure**
  - Keep semantic sections (`header`, `main`, `section`, `footer`) and reuse existing section patterns (like `sec-title`, `container`, etc.).
  - When adding new sections, follow existing indentation and class naming conventions (use kebab-case, e.g. `courses-section`).
  - Avoid inline styles; move styling into Tailwind classes or component utilities.

- **CSS / Tailwind**
  - Add shared styles inside the existing `@layer components` or `@layer base` blocks in `src/style.css`.
  - Use `@apply` with Tailwind utility classes instead of custom declarations whenever possible.
  - Keep custom colors aligned with theme variables defined in `@theme` (e.g. `--color-primary`, `--color-sc`).

- **JavaScript**
  - Put all interactive behavior in `src/main.js`.
  - Use plain JS (no extra frameworks) unless explicitly introduced later.
  - Prefer small, reusable functions and avoid polluting the global scope.

- **Assets**
  - Place images under `src/images/` and reference them with relative URLs starting from project root (e.g. `/src/images/...`).

- **General**
  - Keep code formatted consistently; follow existing spacing and indentation.
  - Before large refactors, preserve current behavior; make visual changes incrementally.


